y | volume = 10 | issue = 11 | pages = 739\u201342 | date = June 2005 | pmid = 15922927 | doi = 10.1016/S1359-6446(05)03468-9 }}\n* {{cite web | url = https://archive.fortune.com/magazines/fortune/fortune_archive/2003/01/20/335643/index.htm | title = The $10 Billion Pill Hold the fries, please. Lipitor, the cholesterol-lowering medication, has become the bestselling pharmaceutical in history. Here's how Pfizer did it | work = [[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] | first = John | last = Simons | name-list-format = vanc | date = 20 January 2003 }}\n* {{cite news | url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB948677773420632448 | title = The Birth of a Blockbuster: Lipitor's Route out of the Lab | last = Winslow | first = Ron | name-list-format = vanc | date = 24 January 2000 | work = [[The Wall Street Journal]] | access-date = 26 October 2011 | url-access = subscription}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web| url = https://druginfo.nlm.nih.gov/drugportal/name/atorvastatin | publisher = U.S. National Library of Medicine| work = Drug Information Portal| title = Atorvastatin }}\n\n{{Statins}}\n{{Portal bar | Pharmacy and pharmacology | Medicine}}\n\n[[Category:Anilides]]\n[[Category:Diols]]\n[[Category:Fluoroarenes]]\n[[Category:Isopropyl compounds]]\n[[Category:Pfizer brands]]\n[[Category:Pyrroles]]\n[[Category:Statins]]\n[[Category:RTT]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Cholesterol-lowering medication}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox drug\n| Verifiedfields =\n| Watchedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 477861573\n| drug_name         = \n| INN               = \n| type              = <!-- empty -->\n| image = Atorvastatin.svg\n| width = 275\n| alt               = \n| image2 = Atorvastatin-3D-balls.png\n| width2 = 250\n| alt2              = \n| caption           = \n\n<!-- Clinical data -->\n| pronounce = {{IPAc-en|\u0259|\u02cc|t|\u0254r|v|\u0259|\u02c8|s|t|\u00e6|t|\u0259n}}\n| tradename = Lipitor, Sortis, others\n| Drugs.com = {{drugs.com|monograph